name: Percé Rock (Rocher Percé)
description:
Percé Rock (French: Rocher Percé, lit. 'pierced rock') is a huge sheer rock formation in the Gulf of Saint Lawrence on the tip of the Gaspé Peninsula in Québec, Canada, off Percé Bay. Percé Rock appears from a distance like a ship under sail.

This one was later relocated on the right side of the Quebec Flag.
